<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 7:17AM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Perry,
southern Wayne and northwestern Greene Counties through 800 AM CDT...
At 716 AM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm over Sunrise, or 5 miles southeast of Petal,
moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Waynesboro, Richton, Clara, State Line and Buckatunna.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for southwestern
Alabama...and southeastern Mississippi.</instruction>
